mxCell.value: Set ambientPressure link’s mSourcePressure to the ambient pressure from your atmosphere model (based on altitude, etc.) This constrains Node 8 to represent the ambient pressure for overboard flows.
Simplified space shuttle-style pressure control system. Passively maintains the cabin at 14.7 psia with N2 or O2 via the gas select valve.
Typical spacecraft cabin air: 14.7 psi, 70 F, 50% RH, 2 mmHg CO2
LiOH cannisters for controlling CO2 and H2O, compounds configured in input file.
Non-condensing heat exchanger and bypass valve for cabin temperature control
